<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-08-15T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-08-15T14:00:00-05:00" n="148" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">175.1/43: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Vice Consul at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cobb</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-08-15T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 15,
                                        1923—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your August 11, 2 p.m.</p>
                        <p>You may inform High Commission that until Allied Treaty with Turkey is
                            ratified and an agreement between the United States and Great Britain
                            regarding recognition of British mandate in Palestine is arrived at the
                            Department trusts that the terms of the arrangement between the British
                            Legal Secretary and your office will be followed.</p>
                        <p>The Department is taking the matter up with London.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
